how to read papers = 

Pass 1 — 10 minutes:
  Read: Title, Abstract, Conclusion, Figure captions
  Goal: Understand WHAT they did and WHAT they found

Pass 2 — 30 minutes:
  Read: Introduction, Results/Experiments section
  Goal: Understand WHY they did it and HOW well it worked

Pass 3 — Full read (only for the most relevant papers):
  Read: Everything including Methods
  Goal: Understand HOW they did it
  Do this for: FlyWire paper, PPO paper, Peng 2018

For your project specifically:
  When reading any paper ask yourself:
  1. How does their environment compare to ours?
  2. How does their network compare to ours?
  3. What metrics do they report? (we should report same)
  4. What would they say about sparse connectome approach?

